SIMPLE: figuline
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Figuline
<hw>Fig"u*line</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>figulina</ets> pottery, fr. <ets>figulus</ets>. See
<er>Figulate</er>.]</ety> <def>A piece of pottery ornamented with
representations of natural objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whose <qex>figulines</qex> and rustic wares⟦br⟧
Scarce find him bread from day to day.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figuline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Figuline
<hw>Fig"u*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>figulinus</ets>. See <er>Figulate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Suitable for the making of pottery; fictile; -- said of
clay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made of clay, as by the potter; -- said of vessels,
ornamental figures, or the like; <as>as, <ex>figuline</ex>
ware</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Figurability</ent>⟦br⟧
